  "prompt": "How can I record video with Drift Ghost-S while charging?",
  "response": "The Drift Ghost-S is designed to allow you to record video while charging, which is a useful feature for extended recording sessions. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### Steps to Record Video While Charging:\n1. **Prepare Your Equipment**:\n   - Ensure you have a compatible USB cable and a power source (such as a power bank, wall charger, or car charger).\n\n2. **Connect the Power Source**:\n   - Plug the USB cable into the Drift Ghost-S and connect the other end to your power source.\n\n3. **Power On the Camera**:\n   - Turn on the Drift Ghost-S. It should detect the power source and begin charging.\n\n4. **Start Recording**:\n   - Press the record button to start recording. The camera will continue to record while charging.\n\n5. **Monitor the Battery**:\n   - Keep an eye on the battery indicator to ensure the camera is charging properly during recording.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Use a Reliable Power Source**: Ensure the power source provides adequate power to both charge the battery and operate the camera.\n- **Avoid Overheating**: Extended recording sessions while charging may cause the camera to overheat. If the camera feels excessively hot, pause recording and let it cool down.\n- **Check Compatibility**: Use the original or a high-quality USB cable to ensure proper charging and data transfer.\n\n### Troubleshooting:\n- If the camera doesn\u2019t charge while recording, try a different power source or cable.\n- Ensure the camera\u2019s firmware is up to date, as updates may improve charging functionality.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to record video with your Drift Ghost-S while keeping it charged.",
